# SEO & meta

Personal brand first. Hub titles in `consts.ts` are **full SEO strings** — `PageLayout` does not append `| Rafael Roman`. Articles/talks/work/topics layouts set their own title patterns.

## Head.astro

- Default OG: `SITE.OG_IMAGE` (`/og-default.png`) + `og:image:width/height`
- RSS: `<link rel="alternate" href="/rss.xml">`
- Articles: `ogType="article"` + `article={{ publishedTime, tags, author }}`
- JSON-LD: `jsonLd` prop → `JsonLd.astro` (supports array)

## Schema map (`src/lib/seo.ts`)

| Page | Schema helpers |
|------|----------------|
| `/` | `personSchema`, `webSiteSchema` |
| `/articles/*` | `articleSchema`, `breadcrumbSchema` |
| `/speaking/*` | `eventSchema`, `breadcrumbSchema` |
| `/work/*` | `breadcrumbSchema` |
| `/topics/*` | `collectionPageSchema`, `breadcrumbSchema` |

## Related linking (`src/lib/related.ts`)

Resolve frontmatter slug arrays → `RelatedLinks.astro`. Always wire bidirectional links when adding content.

## Verify

Built HTML must have: single `og:type`, `og:image`, `application/ld+json`. Use browser or built `dist/`, not `web_fetch` (strips scripts).

## Don't

- Tag archive pages until 3+ articles per tag
- Thin programmatic pages (body required on talks/work/topics)
- Duplicate homepage title suffix
